    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-09-04T18:20:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-09-04T18:20:00-05:00" n="656"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d656">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">340.280/9–453: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 656<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Lebanon</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d656fn1">Identified also as telegram <gloss
                            target="#t_CRANE1">CRANE</gloss> 19; repeated to Amman as 102, Damascus
                        as 73, and Tel Aviv as 190, and by pouch to Cairo, Baghdad, and
                        Jidda.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-09-04T19:20:00-04:00"
                            >September 4, 1953—7:20 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>316. Have considered <gloss target="#t_RECNE1">RECNE</gloss> reactions <gloss
                        target="#t_TVA1">TVA</gloss> study and Jordan–Yarmuk proposal and wish make
                    following observations and define present policy line.</p>
                <pb facs="1339" n="1299" xml:id="pg_1299"/>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">Observations</hi>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Facts available to <gloss target="#t_TVA1">TVA</gloss> are based on
                        available data, much of it accumulation of precise engineering studies, well
                        as <persName corresp="#p_BME1">Bunger</persName>’s preliminary data.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Experience and knowledge brought to bear by <gloss target="#t_TVA1"
                            >TVA</gloss> and Chas. T. Main is most unlikely to be refuted by
                        subsequent studies; we may safely assume that general magnitude of costs of
                        Maqarin high dam, and value of Maqarin reservoir as a regulator as compared
                        with Tiberias, are now authoritatively determined.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Report itself will be available shortly for study and field comments as to
                        its merits should await detailed study.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>We may conclude that we shall be presented with these alternatives: <list>
                            <label>A.</label>
                            <item>Follow line advocated Amman mission; commit additional $60/70
                                million for Maqarin high dam, requiring five to eight years and
                                secure fewer benefits than would result from development along lines
                                suggested by <gloss target="#t_TVA1">TVA</gloss>, at same time
                                freeing Israel to take unilateral action on waters under <gloss
                                    target="#t_IG1">IG</gloss> physical control;</item>
                            <label>B.</label>
                            <item>Follow line suggested by interpretation facts <gloss
                                    target="#t_TVA1">TVA</gloss> report, as supported by Senate
                                Subcommittee, and endeavor search for formulae which would permit
                                development of water resources on economic lines.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>In either case it will be noted that there are elements in <gloss
                        target="#t_TVA1">TVA</gloss> proposals indentical with plans of <gloss
                        target="#t_TCA1">TCA</gloss> Jordan, which could be carried out soon as
                    surveyed without prejudice eventual decision; and that <gloss target="#t_TVA1"
                        >TVA</gloss> recommends dam Maqarin of intermediate height for power but not
                    for storage.</p>
                <p>As <gloss target="#t_RECNE1">RECNE</gloss> points out decision need not be made
                    until Harza survey completed but preponderance of evidence suggests that
                    eventual decision will be against commitment of time and funds required for
                    Maqarin high dam.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">Policy Line</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Present decision of Department and <gloss target="#t_FOA1">FOA</gloss> made by
                    Secretary and <persName corresp="#p_SHE1">Stassen</persName> is to encourage
                    dissemination of facts as presented by <gloss target="#t_TVA1">TVA</gloss>
                    report and to consider our future course after full import this document is
                    understood by Arabs and Israelis.</p>
                <p>Following receipt initial printed copies <persName corresp="#p_BDC1"
                        >Bergus</persName> should seek <persName corresp="#p_CLJ1"
                    >Carver</persName>’s agreement regarding dissemination of Report and Amman must
                    somehow find way to stimulate Jordanian interest in a proposal which we are
                    certain would bring Jordan and its refugees earlier and more substantial
                    benefits than other known proposals.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF2">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
